Data Cleaning

rent_summary <- rent %>%
  filter(year >= 2000, beds == 2) %>%
  select(year, county, price) %>%
  group_by(year, county) %>%
  summarize(avg_price = mean(price)) %>%
  mutate(county = stringr::str_to_title(county))

construction_summary <- new_construction %>%
  select(year, county, totalproduction) %>%
  group_by(year, county) %>%
  summarize(total_production = sum(totalproduction)) %>%
  mutate(county = gsub(" County", "", county))

merged_data <- left_join(rent_summary, construction_summary, by = c("year", "county")) %>%
  na.omit() %>%
  mutate(rent_price_percentage_change = (avg_price - lag(avg_price)) / lag(avg_price) * 100)

merged_data

new_constr <- new_construction %>%
  select(-c(the_geom,the_geom_webmercator, cartodb_id, source, totalproduction)) %>% filter(year >= 2000) %>%
  group_by(year) %>% pivot_longer(cols = c("sfproduction", "mfproduction", "mhproduction"), names_to = "production_type", values_to = "no_of_houses") %>% mutate(production_type = as.factor(production_type)) %>% mutate(county = gsub(" County", "", county))

Visualisations

1.1 Area Plot

plot_qn1.1 <- new_constr %>%
  ggplot() + 
geom_area(aes(year, no_of_houses, fill = production_type)) + 
facet_wrap(~county, scales = "free_y")

plot_qn1.1 + 
  labs(title = "Annual Production of New Housing by County", fill = "Type of Housing Produced") + 
  xlab("Year") + ylab("Number of New Housing") + 
theme_minimal() +
  scale_fill_discrete(labels = c("Multi-Family", "Mobile Home", "Single-Family")) +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))

### 1.2 Heatmap

heatmap_rent <- na.omit(merged_data) %>%
  filter(year > 2000)

ggplot(heatmap_rent, aes(x = year, y = county, fill = rent_price_percentage_change)) +
  geom_tile() +
  scale_fill_gradient2(
    low = "maroon", mid = "white", high = "darkblue",
    midpoint = 0, limits = c(min(heatmap_rent$rent_price_percentage_change),
                             max(heatmap_rent$rent_price_percentage_change))) +
  labs(title = "Percentage Change in Rent Prices Across County",
       x = "Year",
       y = "County",
       fill = "Percentage Change in Rent Price (%)") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1))

### 1.3 Barplot + Scatterplot

library(ggplot2)
library(ggthemes)

ggplot(merged_data, aes(x = year, y = avg_price)) +
  geom_col(aes(y=total_production, fill = county), show.legend = FALSE, alpha = 0.4) +
  geom_point(aes(color = county), alpha = 1) +
  geom_smooth(method = "loess", se = FALSE, size = 0.5, color = "maroon") +
  scale_size_continuous(range = c(1, 8)) +
  labs(title = "Rent Prices and New Construction in San Francisco Counties Over Time",
       x = "Year",
       y = "Average Rent Price / Number of New Construction",
       color = "County") +
  theme_calc() +
  facet_wrap(~county, ncol = 3, scales = "free_y")
